hwMstp.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwMstp.description: The mib is used for defining MIB objects of the multiple spanning tree protocol (MSTP). MSTP is an improvement of STP and RSTP. MSTP prevents the proliferation and infinite cycling of the packets in the loop network. In addition, MSTP provides multiple redundant paths for VLAN data transmission to achieve the load-sharing purpose. It supports MSTP loop network that helps meet various networking requirements.

HwMSTPEnabledStatus.name: HwMSTPEnabledStatus
HwMSTPEnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

hwMstpStatus.name: hwMstpStatus
hwMstpStatus.description: Indicates the status of the MSTP function of a bridge. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates the MSTP function of a bridge is enabled 2. disabled(2) -indicates the MSTP function of a bridge is disabled Default: disabled(2)

hwMstpForceVersion.name: hwMstpForceVersion
hwMstpForceVersion.description: Indicates the MSTP version of the current bridge. Options: 1. stp(0) -indicates the MSTP version of the current bridge is stp 2. rstp(2) -indicates the MSTP version of the current bridge is rstp 3. mstp(3) -indicates the MSTP version of the current bridge is mstp Default: mstp(3) rstp(2) is not supported.

hwMstpDiameter.name: hwMstpDiameter
hwMstpDiameter.description: Indicates the diameter of the current bridged network. Range: 2-7 Default: 7

hwMstpBridgeMaxHops.name: hwMstpBridgeMaxHops
hwMstpBridgeMaxHops.description: Indicates the maximum hop count of a region. Range: 1-40 Default: 20

hwMstpMasterBridgeID.name: hwMstpMasterBridgeID
hwMstpMasterBridgeID.description: Indicates the master bridge ID of an IST in an MSTP region. It is the root Bridge Identifier of the instance 0 in the region. The format of the bridge ID is bridge priority (2B) + bridge MAC address (6B). For example, if the bridge priority is 32768, and the bridge MAC address is 00.EE.DC.F9.13.20, then the bridge ID is 80.00.00.EE.DC.F9.13.20.

hwMstpMasterPathCost.name: hwMstpMasterPathCost
hwMstpMasterPathCost.description: Indicates the external path cost. The value range of this leaf is relevant to hwMstpPathCostStandard. Range: 1-65535 (The 802.1d-1998 protocol is used as the computing standard) 1-200000000 (The 802.1t protocol is used as the computing standard) 1-200000 (Huawei's proprietary legacy is used as the computing standard)

hwMstpBpduGuard.name: hwMstpBpduGuard
hwMstpBpduGuard.description: Indicates whether a bridge is enabled with BPDU protection. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates BPDU protection of the bridge is enabled 2. disabled(2) -indicates BPDU protection of the bridge is disabled Default: disabled(2)

hwMstpAdminFormatSelector.name: hwMstpAdminFormatSelector
hwMstpAdminFormatSelector.description: Indicates the configuration ID format of a bridge.

hwMstpAdminRegionName.name: hwMstpAdminRegionName
hwMstpAdminRegionName.description: Indicates the MSTP region name. The region name consists of up to 32 characters, and only letters (case sensitive), numerals, the hyphen (-), and the underline (_) are allowed.

hwMstpAdminRevisionLevel.name: hwMstpAdminRevisionLevel
hwMstpAdminRevisionLevel.description: Indicates the revision level of an MSTP region name. Range: 0-65535 Default: 0

hwMstpOperFormatSelector.name: hwMstpOperFormatSelector
hwMstpOperFormatSelector.description: Indicates the configuration format of the region of a bridge in actual running.

hwMstpOperRegionName.name: hwMstpOperRegionName
hwMstpOperRegionName.description: Indicates the actually-used MSTP region name.

hwMstpOperRevisionLevel.name: hwMstpOperRevisionLevel
hwMstpOperRevisionLevel.description: Indicates the revision level of the actually-used MSTP region name. Default: 0

hwMstpRegionConfActive.name: hwMstpRegionConfActive
hwMstpRegionConfActive.description: Indicates whether to activate the modified MSTP region configuration. Options: 1. enable (1) -when you need to activate the modified MSTP region configuration, use this value to perform the set operation. 2. disable(2) -the modified MSTP region configuration cannot be set to disable. When you perform the get operation to query the configuration, this value will be returned. This leaf supports only the set operation and it is recommended that you do not perform the get operation. If you perform the get operation, the value disable (2) will be returned.

hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo.name: hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo
hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo.description: Sets the default mapping between VLANs and spanning trees. Options: 1. enable(1) -indicates the default mapping between VLANs and spanning trees is enabled 2. unused(65535) -indicates the default mapping between VLANs and spanning trees is unused

hwMstpDefaultRegionName.name: hwMstpDefaultRegionName
hwMstpDefaultRegionName.description: Sets the default region name. Options: 1. reset(1) -indicates the default region name is used 2. unused(65535) -indicates the default region name is unused

hwMstpPathCostStandard.name: hwMstpPathCostStandard
hwMstpPathCostStandard.description: Indicates the reference standard for path cost computation of a bridge. Options: 1. dot1d1998(1) -indicates dot1d1998 is the reference standard for path cost computation of a bridge 2. dot1t(2) -indicates dot1t is the reference standard for path cost computation of a bridge 3. legacy(3) -indicates legacy is the reference standard for path cost computation of a bridge Default: legacy(3)

hwMstpTimeFactor.name: hwMstpTimeFactor
hwMstpTimeFactor.description: Indicates the timeout factor of a bridge. Range: 1-10 Default: 3

hwMstpMD5KEY.name: hwMstpMD5KEY
hwMstpMD5KEY.description: Indicates the MD5 key used for generating the region configuration digest of the MSTP protocol. Default: 0x13AC06A62E47FD51F95D2BA243CD0346

hwMstpVIDAllocationTable.name: hwMstpVIDAllocationTable
hwMstpVIDAllocationTable.description: Indicates the mapping between VLANs and instances extended by MSTP. The index of this table is hwMstpVID.

hwMstpVIDAllocationEntry.name: hwMstpVIDAllocationEntry
hwMstpVIDAllocationEntry.description: Indicates the mapping between VLANs and instances extended by MSTP. The index of this entry is hwMstpVID.

hwMstpVID.name: hwMstpVID
hwMstpVID.description: It is an index and indicates the VLAN ID. Range: 1-4094

hwMstpAdminMstID.name: hwMstpAdminMstID
hwMstpAdminMstID.description: Indicates the configured MSTP region ID. Currently, the system supports only 17 instances, that is, instances 0-16. Range: 0-48

hwMstpOperMstID.name: hwMstpOperMstID
hwMstpOperMstID.description: Indicates the MSTP region ID in actual running. Currently, the system supports only 17 instances, that is, instances 0-16. Range: 0-48

hwMstpInstanceTable.name: hwMstpInstanceTable
hwMstpInstanceTable.description: Indicates the instances extended by MSTP. The index of this table is hwMstpInstanceID.

hwMstpInstanceEntry.name: hwMstpInstanceEntry
hwMstpInstanceEntry.description: Indicates the instances extended by MSTP. The index of this entry is hwMstpInstanceID.

hwMstpInstanceID.name: hwMstpInstanceID
hwMstpInstanceID.description: It is an index and indicates the MSTI ID.

hwMstpiBridgeID.name: hwMstpiBridgeID
hwMstpiBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID. The format of the bridge ID is bridge priority (2B) + bridge MAC address (6B). For example, if the bridge priority is 32768, and the bridge MAC address is 00.EE.DC.F9.13.20, then the bridge ID is 80.00.00.EE.DC.F9.13.20.

hwMstpiBridgePriority.name: hwMstpiBridgePriority
hwMstpiBridgePriority.description: Indicates the primary priority of the CIST bridge, or priority of the bridge in others. Range: 0-61440 Default: 32768 Step: 4096

hwMstpiDesignedRoot.name: hwMstpiDesignedRoot
hwMstpiDesignedRoot.description: Indicates the master bridge ID of an MSTI in the region.

hwMstpiRootPathCost.name: hwMstpiRootPathCost
hwMstpiRootPathCost.description: Indicates the cost of the path from the BPDU-transmitting bridge to the root bridge.

hwMstpiRootPort.name: hwMstpiRootPort
hwMstpiRootPort.description: Indicates the root port of an MSTI in the region.

hwMstpiRootType.name: hwMstpiRootType
hwMstpiRootType.description: Indicates the type of the bridge. Options: 1. normal(0) -indicates the bridge is normal 2. secondary(1) -indicates the bridge is secondary 3. primary(2) -indicates the bridge is primary Default: normal(0)

hwMstpiRemainingHops.name: hwMstpiRemainingHops
hwMstpiRemainingHops.description: Indicates the remaining hops of an MSTI in the region.

hwMstpiRowStatus.name: hwMstpiRowStatus
hwMstpiRowStatus.description: Indicates the row status, which is the operation type of the table. Only option createAndGo(4) supports the set operation. In the query operation, the value of this leaf is always active(1). To create an MSTI, optionally input leaves hwMstpiBridgePriority, hwMstpiRootType, hwMstpiAdminMappedVlanListLow, and hwMstpiAdminMappedVlanListHigh, specify the value of hwMstpiRowStatus to createAndGo(4), and perform the set operation. To modify the values of other leaves, you can directly perform the set operation without setting and issuing the row status. Options: 1. active(1) -indicates the query operation 2. createAndGo(4) -indicates creating an MSTI 3. destroy(6) -indicates deleting an MSTI

hwMstpiBridgeSecondaryPriority.name: hwMstpiBridgeSecondaryPriority
hwMstpiBridgeSecondaryPriority.description: Indicates the secondary priority of the CIST bridge. Only used by CIST. Range: 0-61440 Default: 61440 Step: 4096

hwMstpiBridgeSecondaryPriorityBindPort.name: hwMstpiBridgeSecondaryPriorityBindPort
hwMstpiBridgeSecondaryPriorityBindPort.description: Indicates the port which bound secondary priority of the CIST bridge in the region. Only used by CIST. Default: 0

hwMstpiBridgeCurrentPriority.name: hwMstpiBridgeCurrentPriority
hwMstpiBridgeCurrentPriority.description: Indicates the current priority of the bridge, including CIST and others. Range: 0-61440

hwMstpPortTable.name: hwMstpPortTable
hwMstpPortTable.description: Indicates the ports extended by MSTP. The indexes of this table are hwMstpInstanceID and hwMstpiPortIndex.

hwMstpPortEntry.name: hwMstpPortEntry
hwMstpPortEntry.description: Indicates the ports extended by MSTP. The indexes of this entry are hwMstpInstanceID and hwMstpiPortIndex.

hwMstpiPortIndex.name: hwMstpiPortIndex
hwMstpiPortIndex.description: It is an index and indicates a bridge port.

hwMstpiPortState.name: hwMstpiPortState
hwMstpiPortState.description: Indicates the port status. Options: 1. disabled(1) -indicates the port is down 2. discarding(2) -indicates the port is discarding. During this phase, port can only receive and process BPDU data packet, not forward traffic, root bridge, root port, and specified port will be voted 3. learning(4) -indicates the port is learning. During this phase, bridge will create MAC address table according the received traffic, but not forward traffic 4. forwarding(5) -indicates traffic forward

hwMstpiPortPriority.name: hwMstpiPortPriority
hwMstpiPortPriority.description: Indicates the port priority. Range: 0-240 Default: 128 Step: 16

hwMstpiPortPathCost.name: hwMstpiPortPathCost
hwMstpiPortPathCost.description: Indicates the path cost of the port. The value range of this leaf is relevant to hwMstpPathCostStandard. Range: 1-65535 (The 802.1d-1998 protocol is used as the computing standard) 1-200000000 (The 802.1t protocol is used as the computing standard) 1-200000 (Huawei's proprietary legacy is used as the computing standard)

hwMstpiDesignatedRoot.name: hwMstpiDesignatedRoot
hwMstpiDesignatedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the port of the Spanning Tree instance identified by the MSTID. The format of the bridge ID is bridge priority (2B) + bridge MAC address (6B). For example, if the bridge priority is 32768, and the bridge MAC address is 00.EE.DC.F9.13.20, then the bridge ID is 80.00.00.EE.DC.F9.13.20.

hwMstpiDesignatedCost.name: hwMstpiDesignatedCost
hwMstpiDesignatedCost.description: Indicates the cost of the path from the port to the root bridge.

hwMstpiDesignatedBridge.name: hwMstpiDesignatedBridge
hwMstpiDesignatedBridge.description: Indicates the designated bridge. The format of the bridge ID is bridge priority (2B) + bridge MAC address (6B). For example, if the bridge priority is 32768, and the bridge MAC address is 00.EE.DC.F9.13.20, then the bridge ID is 80.00.00.EE.DC.F9.13.20.

hwMstpiDesignatedPort.name: hwMstpiDesignatedPort
hwMstpiDesignatedPort.description: Indicates the designated port. The format of the port ID is port priority (1B) + port number (1B). For example, if the port priority is 128, and the port number is 1, then the port ID is 80.01.

hwMstpiStpPortEdgeport.name: hwMstpiStpPortEdgeport
hwMstpiStpPortEdgeport.description: Indicates whether the current port is an edge port. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates the current port is an edge port 2. disabled(2) -indicates the current port is not an edge port Default: disabled(2)

hwMstpiStpPortPointToPoint.name: hwMstpiStpPortPointToPoint
hwMstpiStpPortPointToPoint.description: Indicates whether the current port is a point-to-point port. Options: 1. forceTrue(1) -indicates the current port is a point-to-point port 2. forceFalse(2) -indicates the current port is not a point-to-point port 3. auto(3) -indicates the current port is a self-negotiation port Default: auto(3)

hwMstpiStpMcheck.name: hwMstpiStpMcheck
hwMstpiStpMcheck.description: Indicates the mcheck parameter of the bridge port. Options: 1. enable(1) -indicates the mcheck parameter of the bridge port is enabled 2. unused(65535) -indicates the mcheck parameter of the bridge port is unused

hwMstpiStpTransLimit.name: hwMstpiStpTransLimit
hwMstpiStpTransLimit.description: Indicates the maximum number of BPDUs that can be transmitted within the hello time. Range: 1-255 Default: 3

hwMstpiStpRXStpBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpRXStpBPDU
hwMstpiStpRXStpBPDU.description: Indicates the number of BPDUs received by the port.

hwMstpiStpTXStpBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpTXStpBPDU
hwMstpiStpTXStpBPDU.description: Indicates the number of BPDUs transmitted by the port.

hwMstpiStpRXTCNBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpRXTCNBPDU
hwMstpiStpRXTCNBPDU.description: Indicates the number of TCN BPDUs received by the port.

hwMstpiStpTXTCNBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpTXTCNBPDU
hwMstpiStpTXTCNBPDU.description: Indicates the number of TCN BPDUs transmitted by the port.

hwMstpiStpRXRSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpRXRSTPBPDU
hwMstpiStpRXRSTPBPDU.description: Indicates the number of RST BPDUs received by the port.

hwMstpiStpTXRSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpTXRSTPBPDU
hwMstpiStpTXRSTPBPDU.description: Indicates the number of RST BPDUs transmitted by the port.

hwMstpiStpRXMSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpRXMSTPBPDU
hwMstpiStpRXMSTPBPDU.description: Indicates the number of MST BPDUs received by the port.

hwMstpiStpTXMSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpiStpTXMSTPBPDU
hwMstpiStpTXMSTPBPDU.description: Indicates the number of MST BPDUs transmitted by the port.

hwMstpiStpClearStatistics.name: hwMstpiStpClearStatistics
hwMstpiStpClearStatistics.description: Indicates whether to clear the statistics. Options: 1. clear(1) -indicates the statistics is cleared 2. unused(65535) -indicates the statistics is not cleared

hwMstpiStpDefaultPortCost.name: hwMstpiStpDefaultPortCost
hwMstpiStpDefaultPortCost.description: Indicates whether to restore the default port cost. Options: 1. reset(1) -indicates the default port cost is restored 2. unused(65535) -indicates the default port cost is not restored

hwMstpiStpStatus.name: hwMstpiStpStatus
hwMstpiStpStatus.description: Indicates whether STP is enabled on the port. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates STP is enabled on the port 2. disabled(2) -indicates STP is not enabled on the port Default: enabled(1)

hwMstpiPortRootGuard.name: hwMstpiPortRootGuard
hwMstpiPortRootGuard.description: Indicates whether root protection is enabled on the port. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates root protection is enabled on the port 2. disabled(2) -indicates root protection is disabled on the port Default: disabled(2)

hwMstpiPortLoopGuard.name: hwMstpiPortLoopGuard
hwMstpiPortLoopGuard.description: Indicates whether loop protection is enabled on the port. Options: 1. enabled(1) -indicates loop protection is enabled on the port 2. disabled(2) -indicates loop protection is disabled on the port Default: disabled(2)

hwMstpiPortCompliance.name: hwMstpiPortCompliance
hwMstpiPortCompliance.description: Indicates the MSTP compliance type of the current port. Options: 1. auto(1) -indicates the MSTP compliance type of the current port is auto 2. dot1w(2) -indicates the MSTP compliance type of the current port is dot1w Default: auto(1).

hwMstpiPortStateForwarding.name: hwMstpiPortStateForwarding
hwMstpiPortStateForwarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into forwarding state form other state.

hwMstpiPortStateDiscarding.name: hwMstpiPortStateDiscarding
hwMstpiPortStateDiscarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into discarding state form forwarding state.

hwMstpiPortRootGuarded.name: hwMstpiPortRootGuarded
hwMstpiPortRootGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a root-guard port receives a superior message on the relevant instance.

hwMstpiPortRootGuardedResume.name: hwMstpiPortRootGuardedResume
hwMstpiPortRootGuardedResume.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a root-guard port not receives a superior message on the relevant instance.

hwMstpiPortBpduGuarded.name: hwMstpiPortBpduGuarded
hwMstpiPortBpduGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an edged port of the BPDU-guard switch receives BPDU packets.

hwMstpiPortBpduGuardedResume.name: hwMstpiPortBpduGuardedResume
hwMstpiPortBpduGuardedResume.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an edged port of the BPDU-guard switch not receives BPDU packets.

hwMstpiPortDisable.name: hwMstpiPortDisable
hwMstpiPortDisable.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port disable stp.

hwMstpBridgeInfoGroup.name: hwMstpBridgeInfoGroup
hwMstpBridgeInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects indicating the necessary capabilites of the bridge device which is running the multi spanning tree protocol.

hwMstpVlanInfoGroup.name: hwMstpVlanInfoGroup
hwMstpVlanInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects describes the attribute of the vlan in the multi spanning tree protocol. They are necessary to find the relation between vlan and instance by the vlan identifier.

hwMstpInstanceInfoGroup.name: hwMstpInstanceInfoGroup
hwMstpInstanceInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects describes the attribute of the instance in the multi spanning tree protocol.

hwMstpPortInfoGroup.name: hwMstpPortInfoGroup
hwMstpPortInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects is necessary to show the information of the port in the bridge in the multi spanning tree protocol.

hwMstpCompliance.name: hwMstpCompliance
hwMstpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for device support of Priority and Multicast Filtering extended bridging services.
